<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,921,1014,1077]" box="[151,299,1051,1077]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,290,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[156,1437,191,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[150,1437,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7.—Pantoporia bieti aurantina Monastyrskii &amp; To, subspec. nov. A–B—♀HT, central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; C–D—P. b. paona Tytler, 1915, Type, ♀, Kirbari, Naga Hills; E–F—P. b. bieti (Oberthür, 1894), Type, ♂, western China, Ta-Tsien-Lou" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556618/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Figs. 7A, B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1122,1761]" box="[151,766,1122,1149]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,299,1122,1148]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Description:</emphasis>
Female: Length of forewing: HT 
<quantity box="[679,761,1122,1149]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1122,1761]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,467,1158,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Both wings upperside.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[482,601,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[156,1437,191,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[150,1437,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7.—Pantoporia bieti aurantina Monastyrskii &amp; To, subspec. nov. A–B—♀HT, central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; C–D—P. b. paona Tytler, 1915, Type, ♀, Kirbari, Naga Hills; E–F—P. b. bieti (Oberthür, 1894), Type, ♂, western China, Ta-Tsien-Lou" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556618/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Figure 7A</figureCitation>
) Ground colour is black; all spots and bands are uniformly bright orange, including large discal cell streak merged with the streak beyond discal cell; lower postdiscal large spots in cells A1+A2 and Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[323,338,1249,1263]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">1a</subScript>
are connected in cell Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[615,632,1249,1263]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">1b</subScript>
;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1122,1761]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1266,1293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Both wings underside.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[480,596,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[156,1437,191,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[150,1437,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7.—Pantoporia bieti aurantina Monastyrskii &amp; To, subspec. nov. A–B—♀HT, central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; C–D—P. b. paona Tytler, 1915, Type, ♀, Kirbari, Naga Hills; E–F—P. b. bieti (Oberthür, 1894), Type, ♂, western China, Ta-Tsien-Lou" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556618/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Figure 7B</figureCitation>
) Ground colour of both wings dark reddish brown; all spots and bands are yellow; markings broad and distinct; wing patterns similar to those on the upperside except for a series of distinct pale violet subcostal spots in cells R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[557,565,1357,1371]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[598,606,1357,1371]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">2</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[639,647,1357,1371]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[726,734,1357,1371]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">1</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="496" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1122,1761]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1374,1400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The new taxon may be distinguished from individuals of other subspecies distributed in western 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1411,1437]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">China</collectingCountry>
(the nominate subspecies) (
<figureCitation box="[528,674,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[156,1437,191,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[150,1437,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7.—Pantoporia bieti aurantina Monastyrskii &amp; To, subspec. nov. A–B—♀HT, central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; C–D—P. b. paona Tytler, 1915, Type, ♀, Kirbari, Naga Hills; E–F—P. b. bieti (Oberthür, 1894), Type, ♂, western China, Ta-Tsien-Lou" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556618/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Figure 7E–F</figureCitation>
), Naga Hills and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1061,1411,1437]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1249,1411,1437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="paona">
subspec. 
<emphasis box="[1179,1249,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">paona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1425,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[156,1437,191,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[150,1437,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7.—Pantoporia bieti aurantina Monastyrskii &amp; To, subspec. nov. A–B—♀HT, central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; C–D—P. b. paona Tytler, 1915, Type, ♀, Kirbari, Naga Hills; E–F—P. b. bieti (Oberthür, 1894), Type, ♂, western China, Ta-Tsien-Lou" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556618/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Figure 7C–D</figureCitation>
). It has well developed, broad, bright orange markings on the upperside of both wings, while the other subspecies have whitish (eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[399,461,1483,1509]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Tibet</collectingRegion>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bozano, G. C." box="[473,631,1483,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref11908" refString="Bozano, G. C. (2008) In: Bozano, G. C. (Ed.), Guide to the Butterflies of the Palearctic Region. Nymphalidae Part III. Subfamily Limenitidinae, Tribe Neptini. Omnes Artes, Milano, pp. 1 - 77." type="book chapter" year="2008">Bozano, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) or yellowish markings (the nominate 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1228,1483,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="from">subspec. from</taxonomicName>
central 
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1388,1483,1509]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,326,1519,1545]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="paona">
subspec. 
<emphasis box="[256,326,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">paona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[546,604,1519,1545]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">India</collectingCountry>
(ex 
<taxonomicName box="[658,793,1519,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
collection of the NHM). The most unusual character of the new taxon is the well-developed series of subcostal spots on the underside of the forewing. Individuals of other subspecies either lack this character or it is unclear. In addition, subcostal spots on the forewing are not typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,279,1627,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pantoporia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Pantoporia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This character is usually observed in some 
<taxonomicName box="[774,846,1627,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Neptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,846,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Neptis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with orange markings, such as the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1876" box="[1240,1349,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Neptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armandia">
<emphasis box="[1240,1349,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">armandia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1363,1436,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">themis</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[199,291,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">antilope</emphasis>
groups.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
